The hAdV genotypes detected in ocular swabs were B03 (n = 79; 68%), E04 (18; 15%), D37 (15; 13%), D19 (4; 3%) and D08 (1; 1%). The hAdV genotypes detected in respiratory (NP in Fig. 4
) specimens were B03 (n = 40; 47%), C02 (19; 22%), C01 (11; 13%), E04 (10; 12%), C05 (3; 4%) and C06 (2; 2%) (Fig. 4). Human AdV infections were prevalent throughout the year but peaked in September and October 2010 (Fig. 5
).
